rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that contains entities representing academic years, i.e. the periods from fall of one year to spring of the next year in which an educational institution is in regular session.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Academic Year

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A system in which relatively long periods of time are named and related to one another. Typically, the periods are days, weeks, months, and years, and they are aligned with the cycles of the sun or moon.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Calendar System

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a calendar system to one of the days of the week used in the system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Days of Week
Month Names
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: It's not clear what this property means and how it is intended to differ from time.calendar.months. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:time.calendar.months]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a calendar system to one of the months used in the system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Months

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type for collecting information about an entity's chronology or milestones, i.e. important dates and events in the history of the entity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Chronology

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a milestone to the date it occurred.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a milestone to the entity the milestone is about.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Entity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property specifying the milestone itself. For example, a milestone in Microsoft's history is the launch of Xbox.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Milestone

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A ceremony or celebration whose purpose is to remember a person or event, e.g. Victory in Europe Day, whose purpose is to celebrate the surrender of Nazi Germany in World War II.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Commemorative Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type for collecting information about the days when a holiday is observed in a particular location. This type is necessary, because some holidays have varying days of observance depending on the location. This is the case, for example, with Father's Day and Mother's Day or with Divali in Northern India and Southern India. Note that in cases where the date of observance varies from year to year, the following paths should be used: mso:time:recurring_event.instance -> mso:time.event.start_date and mso:time.recurring_event.instance -> mso:time.event.end_date.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Country Observance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property specifying the location or locations that observe the given holiday on the given days of the year.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Country

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property specifying the date or start date when the given location observes the given holiday.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use mso:time.recurring_event.instance -> mso:time.event.start_date to record when a holiday instance begins. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:time.event.start_date]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property specifying day(s) of the year when the given location observes the given holiday.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Day of Year

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property specifying the end date for the observance of the given holiday by the given location. Note that it is not necessary to provide a value for this property in cases where the holiday is celebrated on a single day.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: End Date
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use mso:time.recurring_event.instance -> mso:time.event.end_date to record the end date of a holiday instance. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:time.event.end_date]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing entities corresponding to the seven days of the week, viz. Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, Saturday, and Sunday.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Day Of Week

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a day of the week to a calendar system that makes use of this day.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Calendar System

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a day of the week to a number indicating the order of the day within the week, e.g. Sunday is 1 and Saturday is 7.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sequence Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates whether or not the day of the week is a weekday (property set to 1) or weekend (property set to 0).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Weekday

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing entities corresponding to all of the calendar days of the year, e.g. December 25, April 1, and May 22.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Day Of Year

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a day of the year to a calendar system that makes use of the day.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Calendar

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a day of the year to the corresponding number of the day of the month. For example, in the case of "December 25th", this property would have the value 25.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Day

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a day of the year to a holiday that occurs on that day each year, e.g. December 25 is related to Christmas by this property.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Holidays

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a day of the year to a date that is an instance of the day of the year, e.g. it relates "First Sunday after the first full moon on or after March 21" to March 27, 2016.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Instance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a day of the year to the corresponding month. For example, in the case of "December 25th", this property would have the value "December".
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Month

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a day of the year to the part of the year when the day occurs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Part of Year

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a day of the year to the season of the year when the day occurs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Season

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a day of the year to the sequence number of the week within the year.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Week Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about when daylight saving time begins and ends in a given location.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Daylight Saving Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The day of the year, e.g. second Saturday in October, when daylight saving time begins in a given location.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Beginning of Daylight Saving Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The day of the year, e.g. second Saturday in March, when daylight saving time ends in a given location.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: End of Daylight Saving Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The location for which daylight saving time information is provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Daylight Saving Time Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies a sublocation of the given location that has an exception to the daylight saving time information provided. This information can be retrieved via the property mso:location.location.daylight_saving_time for the sublocation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location Exception

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies in minutes how much daylight savings time differs from standard time for the given location. Note that when no value is provided for this property, the offset is understood to be 60 minutes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Offset

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date, if any, when the given location began to observe daylight saving time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Beginning Date of Observing Daylight Saving Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date, if any, when the given location stopped observing daylight saving time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ending Date of Observing Daylight Saving Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies a time interval that is an exception to the daylight saving time information provided. For example, in some countries, standard time is used during the period of Ramadan.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Time Exception

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type whose instances are characterized by a transient existence, e.g. happenings, processes, actions, celebrations, ticketed events, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an event to the agent (organization or person) who manages or produces the event.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Administrator

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property specifying the broadcaster for the event.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Broadcaster

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links an event to the length of time (in minutes) that the event lasted.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Duration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an event to the date/time, in UTC (Coordinated Universal Time), when the event ends. Note that the property mso:time.event.local_end_date should be used to specify the *local* time when the event ends.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: End Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates that an event has finished. Note that this property should be used only when the date/time of the end of the event is not known. Otherwise, the property time.event.end_date should be used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ended

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an event to another event that precedes it, e.g. the halftime show of the 2014 Superbowl to the first half of the Superbowl.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Following Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an event to another event that contains it, e.g. a music concert includes the performance of a selection of songs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Including Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates an event to a part of the event, e.g. the performance of a song is part of a music concert.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Included Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an event to the *local* date/time when the event ends. Note that the property mso:time.event.end_date should be used to specify the time when the event ends in UTC (Coordinated Universal Time).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Local End Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an event to the *local* date/time when the event begins. Note that the property mso:time.event.start_date should be used to specify the time when the event begins in UTC (Coordinated Universal Time).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Local Start Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an event to a location where the event happened. Although this property is multi-valued, it is best to use only the most specific location. For example, with respect to the assassination of Abraham Lincoln, the best location would be Ford's Theatre. Washington, DC would also be acceptable, but the United States, while strictly accurate, would be a poor choice for location.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an event to a textual description of details about where the event takes place. This is useful in cases where, for example, an event takes place in a particular room of a building.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location Details

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:time.event to the mso:organization.organization that participates in the event.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Organization Participating

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an event to a person who participates in the event.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Person

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an event to another event that follows it, e.g. the first half of the 2014 Superbowl to the halftime show of the Superbowl.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Preceding Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates an event to a recurring event of which it is an instance.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recurring Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an event to a textual description of the outcome of the event.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Result

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an event to the date/time, in UTC (Coordinated Universal Time), when the event begins. Note that the property mso:time.event.local_start_date should be used to specify the *local* time when the event begins.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Start Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an event to the status of the event, e.g. planned, postponed or cancelled.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Status

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of feast days. Feast Days are the days of the year associated with a given saint. These were originally the annual commemorations of martyrs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Feast Day

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing entities corresponding to standard subdivisions of the earth's history for purposes of describing the age of rocks and geologic events. Two examples of geologic periods are the Jurassic and Cambrian periods.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Geologic Time Period

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a geologic time period to information about when, in millions of years ago, that the period began.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Began

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a geologic time period to information about when, in millions of years ago, that the period ended.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ended

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type for collecting information about the estimate of the number of millions of years ago that a time period occurred and the uncertainty of this estimate, also expressed as a number of millions of years.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Geologic Time Period Uncertainty

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a geologic time period to the best estimate for how long ago, in millions of years, that the period occurred.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Millions of Years Ago

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a geologic time period to the uncertainty (plus or minus millions of years) of the best estimate for how long ago, in millions of years, that the period occurred.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Uncertainty

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all holidays. These are the days that are typically taken off of work by law or custom. Holidays may be religious or secular in nature.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Holiday

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a holiday to an agent who celebrates the holiday, e.g. the vegetarian community, an ethnic group, people who embrace a particular philosophical principle, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Celebrant

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a holiday to a description of a way in which the holiday is celebrated.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Celebration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a holiday to a color that is traditionally associated with the holiday.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Color

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a holiday to information about the days when the holiday is observed in a particular country. This property is necessary, because some holidays have varying times of observance depending on the country. This is the case, for example, with Father's Day and Mother's Day. In cases where the holiday is observed on the same day(s) around the world, the property mso:time.holiday.day_of_year should be used. In cases where the date of observance varies from year to year, the following paths should be used: mso:time:recurring_event.instance -> mso:time.event.start_date and mso:time.recurring_event.instance -> mso:time.event.end_date.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Country Observance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a holiday to the day(s) of the year when the holiday is observed, e.g. Christmas is observed on December 25th each year.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Day Of Year
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use the more general property mso:time.recurring_event.occurrance_calendar_day instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:time.recurring_event.occurrance_calendar_day]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a holiday to the religions that observe the holiday, e.g. the holiday of Christmas is celebrated by Christians.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Featured in Religions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a holiday to a standard descriptor for a type of holiday, e.g. public holiday.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Holiday Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a holiday to the holiday season that includes it, e.g. Christmas is part of the Christmas season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Holiday Period

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:time.holiday to the mso:location.location(s) that celebrate the holiday.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Locations

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a holiday to an event that is associated with the holiday, e.g. the Feast of the Immaculate Conception is related to the immaculate conception of Jesus Christ.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Related Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:time.holiday to the mso:food.food that is traditionally associated with the holiday.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Foods

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard, general descriptors for holidays, e.g. Federal Holiday and Religious Holiday.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Holiday Category

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating a holiday category to a holiday that falls under the category.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Holidays

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A period of time spanning several days or even weeks that includes one or more holidays, e.g. the Christmas season or Easter Week.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Holiday Period

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating a holiday period to a holiday that is celebrated during the period.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Holidays

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing entities corresponding to the twelve months of the year, viz. January, February, March, April, May, June, July, August, September, October, November, and December.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Month

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a month to a calendar system that makes use of the month.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Calendar System

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a month to a number indicating the order of the month within the year, e.g. January is 1 and December is 12.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Month Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a month to the number of days in the month, e.g. December has 31 days and September has 30 days.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number Of Days In Month

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration of conventional parts of the year, viz. first quarter, second quarter, third quarter, fourth quarter, first half, and second half.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Part of Year

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: January through June of the year.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: First Half

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: January through March of the year.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: First Quarter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value representing a financial reporting period for an organization.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fiscal Period

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: October through December of the year.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fourth Quarter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value representing twelve months of the year.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Full Year

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: July through December of the year.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Second Half

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: April through June of the year.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Second Quarter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: July through September of the year.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Third Quarter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all recurring events. These are the events whose instances occur with some frequency, including the Academy Awards, United States presidential elections, and the United States census taking events.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recurring Event

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a recurring event to the agent (organization or person) who manages or produces the recurring event.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Administrator

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a recurring event to the frequency with which the event happens, e.g. weekly, monthly, yearly, every decade, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Frequency

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the number of times per unit (given with the mso:time.recurring_event.current_frequency property) that the event recurs. Note that it is not necessary to set this property if the event recurs once per unit.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Current Frequency Value

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a recurring event to the date of the final instance of the event. Note that this property applies only to events that no longer recur.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date of Final Occurrence

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a recurring event to the date of the first instance of the event.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date of first occurrence

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a recurring event to the most recent date of an instance of the recurring event. Note that the meaning of this property is different from mso:time.recurring_event.date_of_final_occurance.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date of Last Occurance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a recurring event to the date of the next instance of the event.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date of Next Occurance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating and mso:time.recurring_event to its mso:event.event_type. For example, the US Presidential Election is a recurring event whose event type is 'US election', or Bumbershoot is a music festival.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Event Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:time.recurring_event to its founder. For example, Bumbershoot was founded by the city of Seattle, and the Academy Awards were founded by Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Founder

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a recurring event to one of its instances, e.g. the Superbowl 2014 is an instance of the Superbowl, which occurs each year.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Instance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a recurring event to a language in which the recurring event is conducted.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Language

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:time.recurring_event to the mso:location.location at which the event recurs. For recurring events that happen at various locations, each instance of the event should be related to a location via the property mso:time.event.location.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the total number of times that the recurring event happens.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number of Instances

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:time.recurring_event to the calendar day when it happens. For example, Thanksgiving in the United States takes place on the fourth Thursday in November.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the part of the year, e.g. the first quarter of the year, during which the event recurs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Part of Year

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that is used in the case of regular recurring events to specify the time when the recurring event begins. For example, in the case of Advent, this would be the fourth Sunday before Christmas.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Range Begin Day

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that is used in the case of regular recurring events to specify the time when the recurring event ends. For example, in the case of Advent, this would be the last Sunday before Christmas.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Range End Day

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a recurring event to one of its recurring subevents. For example, the NASCAR Cup series has regular recurring subevents like the Bad Boy Off Road 300.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recurring Subevent

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates the recurring event does not correspond to fixed dates but can be computed using a standard formula, relative to a fixed date. Note that this property should be used in conjunction with mso:time.recurring_event.range_begin_day and mso:time.recurring_event.range_end_day. An example of a regular recurring event is Advent, which occurs between the fourth Sunday before Christmas and the last Sunday before Christmas.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Regular

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing the four temperate seasons of the year, viz. winter, spring, summer, and autumn.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Season of the Year

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type for storing times of day, e.g. 3 AM or 4 O'clock in the afternoon.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Time of Day

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that specifies whether or not the time indicated is PM. If the Boolean property is not set, then the time indicated is AM or is given using a 24-hour clock.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Afternoon

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a time of day to the day of the week, e.g. Friday, that contains it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Day of Week

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the day of year, if any, associated with the time of day.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Day of Year

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the hour of the time, e.g. 3 in 3:16 PM. Note that this hour can specified with either a 12-hour clock or a 24-hour clock.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hour

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the minutes of the time, e.g. 16 in 3:16 PM.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Minute

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the second of the time, e.g. 42 in 3:16:42 PM.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Second

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a time of day to the timezone, if any, for which the time of day is valid.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Timezone

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the year, if any, associated with the time of day.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Year

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A region that has a single standard time that is defined as an offset from Coordinated Universal Time (UTC). For example, the contiguous United States is divided into four time zones, viz. Eastern Time, Central Time, Mountain Time, and Pacific Time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Time Zone

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The day that daylight saving time begins in the current schedule. This should usually be entered like \"Second Sunday in April\", rather than a specific date, unless the date is always the same.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Day DST begins

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The day that daylight saving time ends in the current schedule. This should usually be entered like \"Second Sunday in October\", rather than a specific date, unless the date is always the same.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Day DST ends

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Offset in hours from UTC or GMT during non daylight savings time
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Offset from UTC

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing entities corresponding to calendar years in the past or present, e.g. 1892 or 1066.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Year
